  "text": "The overflow state is defined in `envoy/common/conn_pool.h` as `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` (line 98). The overflow condition is emitted from two places in `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`: (1) `newStreamImpl()` (line 284) triggers overflow when pending requests exceed the resource limit, and (2) `attachStreamToClient()` (line 178) triggers overflow when max requests are exceeded. Additionally, `source/common/upstream/conn_pool_map_impl.h` increments the `upstream_cx_pool_overflow_` stat (line 38) when connection pool count exceeds the limit. The overflow is then handled by `UpstreamRequest::onPoolFailure` in `source/common/router/upstream_request.cc` (for HTTP routing) and `Filter::onGenericPoolFailure` in `source/common/tcp_proxy/tcp_proxy.cc` (for TCP proxying), both of which translate the overflow reason into appropriate reset/close behaviors.",
